captions.text:
And today, we're going
to be doing a studio

tour in our brand
new house in Texas.

We're going to be doing an
art studio, a brand new one.

It's actually-- I love
the color, by the way.

And so we'll start
with the decorations.

This is our absolutely,
positively adorable couch

It's called "Cute
as a Button" from--

And it's got like a ton of
cute little buttons with--
And it just matches the whole--

-Just brings in all the
different colors and stuff.

-And then this is-- these
flowers are from Hobby Lobby.

And they just bring
together the whole scene.

-And then that's a
pillow from Target.

-And then this is
our board with "B&B"

because we are
Brooklyn and Bailey.

-And Jenny from
ShowMeCute and my mom

Well, actually, they
designed the entire thing.

-And so when they brought us
up here we were so excited.

-We were like, oh my
god, it's so cute!

So then we'll start
with the lighting,

because everyone wonders
what we do with our lighting.

-This is actually
called a soft box.

It's a giant light
that you shine,

and it makes it a lot
brighter in the filming--
This one is called a boom box.

-I'm not sure why
it's called a boom.
so we have to put sand on it.

-Because you don't want
a boom falling on you

-I don't think we've ever
had that incident happen,

-This giant thing is our
beautiful antique cabinet

that we hold
anything that we use.

-This as our beautiful
desk of glory

that we will use
when we use DIYs.
And then we just fixed it up.

-And then like put some
cute dark stains on it
so it looks all nice and empty.

-And it's just got a
really cute floral painting

And we actually just use this
for pictures or interviews.

-Whenever we do our Q&As,
if we do another one,

we'll put chairs right here, and
we'll sit and talk to you with

Now we're going to
CuteGirlsHairstyles studio over

-And in case you're wondering,
it is actually split in half.

and over here is
Brooklyn And Bailey.

-So as you can see,
this is the desk

where my mom films
all of the hairstyles.

And we have our
camera stuff here.

-This is actually something
you hold the camera on.

-You hold it like this, because
the cameras weight a lot.

So when you're filming
for a long time,

you're like, hold slowly the
camera so your arms don't die.

-And so behind here
is where we store

all of like little random stuff,
like lip gloss and brushes

and combs or whatever else my
mom needs for her hair styles.

-Can you see this
chair back here?

This is the spinny
chair of glory

that we spin once my mom is
finished with her hairstyle

This is normally where I would
say it, or CGH3 would say it,

or whoever's getting their
hair done would sit for my mom.

-And then here's
the chair where we
take all of our hair pictures.

-And this is our
glorious old clock

that we got in some
antique store somewhere.
I'm not really sure where, but--

-And as you can see,
my mom's antique fan.

So we have a lot of
antiques around here,

like antique suitcases,
antique desk, antique desk.

-I don't know if
this is antique.

It has different words,
like courage and dream big.

-And once again, Jenny
from ShowMeCute made it.

-And we have our picture
of our family here.

But this is kind of
old, so I'm not sure

if we all look
like that anymore.

This is the only bedroom in
the house that is big enough

for us to put the gym mat
and do our gymnastics on.

-So we have our gym
mat in our studio.

Because it's definitely
fun to see what's
behind the scenes a little bit.

-So you can comment
below on what

you thought of our
brand new studio.

And we will see
you guys next week!
Does it look good on the camera?
